Wrong, they are not allowed to communicate, if they were caught sending signals by being surprised they would loose. here is a hint. Again the prisoners know there are 3 black hats and 2 white hats in play. But how does the individual prisoner come to the conclusion that he has a black hat and not a white hat? If one white hat was in play, two ppl would have seen this white hat, and since noone said anything for a while (seeing two white hats) they would know that they must have a black hat.
